729729f-b.title: Richmond: Thompson Street - Front Street
729729f-b.text:
Thompson Street, at Front Street (vantage point).
The three views are south along the new Staten Island Railroad
embankment llying between Bay Street (right) and Murray Hulbert
Avenue. On the right, across the freight house, are buildings
of the U. S. Marine Hospital on Bay Street. The gas tank is at
Edgewater Street; to its left are the Clifton railroad repair
shops and the spire of St. Mary's R. C. Church, at Rosebank;
still farther left is the Pouch Terminal warehouse, the Wrigley
chewing gum plant, and piers on Murray Hulbert Avenue.
May 25, 1935
Views 1, 2, 3
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
